s enduring appeal and, through its explication oftexts and investigation of the man, demonstrates just why he continues, and should continue, to attract scholarly interest. FEDERICO BONADDIO lectures in Modern Spanish Studies at King's College London. CONTRIBUTORS: FEDERICO BONADDIO, JACQUELINE COCKBURN, NIGEL DENNIS, CHRISTOPHER MAURER, ALBERTO MIRA, ANTONIO MONEGAL, CHRIS PERRIAM, XON DE ROS, ERIC SOUTHWORTH, D. GARETH WALTERS, SARAH WRIGHT  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aHispanic Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aFederico García Lorca.  aSpain.  aSpanish literature.  acinema.  adrawing.  agender.  aiconic poet.  amusic.  apoetry.  apolitics.  areligion.  atheatre.1 aBonaddio, Federico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonaddio, Federico, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCockburn, Jacqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCockburn, Jaqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Ros, Xon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDennis, Nigel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaurer, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMira, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonegal, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerriam, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSouthworth, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalters, D. Gareth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWright, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators